    "recap_text": "LYNCHBURG, VA. \u2013\nDesignated hitter\nJordan Jaffe\ndrove in four runs and starting pitcher\nBradley Zayac\nstruck out a career-high 10 in a 9-3 victory over the Missouri State Bears Sunday at Worthington Field at Liberty Baseball Stadium. With the win, the Flames salvage a game in the three-game series.\nJaffe hit his first home run as a Flame with one aboard to give Liberty the lead in the first inning and knocked in two runs with a single in the second inning. He also scored two runs.\nMeanwhile, Zayac allowed two runs on four hits over six innings. He struck out a career-high 10 and did not walk a batter.\nLiberty, which bounces back after dropping the first two games of the series by one run each, moves to 13-5 overall and 1-2 in CUSA. Missouri State falls 12-7 overall and 2-1 in conference play.\nBox Score Highlights\nRecords:\nMissouri State (12-7, 2-1 CUSA); Liberty (13-5, 1-2 CUSA)\nLocation:\nLynchburg, Va. (Worthington Field at Liberty Baseball Stadium)\nWP:\nBradley Zayac\n(3-0) |\nLP:\nOwen Slater (1-2) |\nSV:\nCooper Harrington\n(1)\nScoring Summary\n1\nst\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Bogenpohl homers, 1-0\n1\nst\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Jaffe homers, Drumm scores, 2-1\n2\nnd\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Carter flies out, Bergman scores, 2-2\n2\nnd\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Jaffe singles, Marsh and Drumm score, 4-2\n4\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Sorenson singles, Jaffe scores, 5-2\n6\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 DeCandido singles, Sorenson scores, 6-2\n6\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Campos flies out, Barone scores, 7-2\n6\nth\n\u2013 LIBERTY \u2013 Drumm singles, Moore and DeCandido score, 9-2\n7\nth\n\u2013 MO ST \u2013 Carter grounds into a double play, Bergman scores, 9-3\nNotable Numbers\n- Liberty outhit Missouri State, 13-7. The Flames committed one error, while the Bears made two in the contest.\n- Liberty left 13 men on base. Missouri State left six.\n- Right fielder\nRyan Drumm\n, catcher\nTucker Moore\nand center fielder\nJosh Campos\neach had two hits in the game.\n- Reliever\nCooper Harrington\ntook over for Zayac in the seventh and proceeded to pitch three scoreless innings to record a save. The right-hander allowed one run on three hits over the final three frames. He struck out four and walked one.\n- Missouri State starting pitcher Owen Slater takes the loss. The right-hander gave up four runs on five hits over 2 2/3-plus innings. He struck one and walked four batters.\n- Designated hitter Carter Bregman went 3-for-4 and scored two runs for the Bears.\n- Center fielder Caden Bogenpohl hit his fourth home run of the year in the contest.\nBeyond the Box Score\n- Liberty records its first CUSA win of the season with the victory. The Flames lost a pair of one-run games to open the series.\n- Jaffe records his fourth multi-hit game of the season and his second multi-hit contest in as many days.\n- Zayac sets a career-high with 10 strikeouts, eclipsing his previous high of seven.\n- With two hits, Campos ties shortstop\nTanner Marsh\nfor the Liberty lead with six multi-hit games. Drumm recorded his fourth.\n- With a single in the second, Marsh extends his hitting streak to 15, setting a new career-high for the junior. He also has reached base in every game this season.\nUp Next\nLiberty travels to Winston-Salem, N.C., for a game against the No. 12 Wake Forest Demon Deacons. The first pitch is scheduled for 6 p.m."
